description: Gets information about one or more compute fleets.

nested_items.name: fleets
nested_items.description: Information about the requested compute fleets.

nested_items.name: arn
nested_items.description: The ARN of the compute fleet.

nested_items.name: name
nested_items.description: The name of the compute fleet.

nested_items.name: id
nested_items.description: The ID of the compute fleet.

nested_items.name: created
nested_items.description: The time at which the compute fleet was created.

nested_items.name: lastModified
nested_items.description: The time at which the compute fleet was last modified.

nested_items.name: statusCode
nested_items.description: The status code of the compute fleet. Valid values include:
CREATING: The compute fleet is being created.
UPDATING: The compute fleet is being updated.
ROTATING: The compute fleet is being rotated.
PENDING_DELETION: The compute fleet is pending deletion.
DELETING: The compute fleet is being deleted.
CREATE_FAILED: The compute fleet has failed to create.
UPDATE_ROLLBACK_FAILED: The compute fleet has failed to update and could not rollback to previous state.
ACTIVE: The compute fleet has succeeded and is active.

nested_items.name: context
nested_items.description: Additional information about a compute fleet. Valid values include:
CREATE_FAILED: The compute fleet has failed to create.
UPDATE_FAILED: The compute fleet has failed to update.

nested_items.name: message
nested_items.description: A message associated with the status of a compute fleet.

nested_items.name: baseCapacity
nested_items.description: The initial number of machines allocated to the compute ï¬eet, which deï¬nes the number of builds that can run in parallel.

nested_items.name: environmentType
nested_items.description: The environment type of the compute fleet.

The environment type ARM_CONTAINER is available only in regions US East (N. Virginia), US East (Ohio), US West (Oregon), EU (Ireland), Asia Pacific (Mumbai), Asia Pacific (Tokyo), Asia Pacific (Singapore), Asia Pacific (Sydney), EU (Frankfurt), and South America (SÃ£o Paulo).

The environment type ARM_EC2 is available only in regions US East (N. Virginia), US East (Ohio), US West (Oregon), EU (Ireland), EU (Frankfurt), Asia Pacific (Tokyo), Asia Pacific (Singapore), Asia Pacific (Sydney), South America (SÃ£o Paulo), and Asia Pacific (Mumbai).

The environment type LINUX_CONTAINER is available only in regions US East (N. Virginia), US East (Ohio), US West (Oregon), EU (Ireland), EU (Frankfurt), Asia Pacific (Tokyo), Asia Pacific (Singapore), Asia Pacific (Sydney), South America (SÃ£o Paulo), and Asia Pacific (Mumbai).

The environment type LINUX_EC2 is available only in regions US East (N. Virginia), US East (Ohio), US West (Oregon), EU (Ireland), EU (Frankfurt), Asia Pacific (Tokyo), Asia Pacific (Singapore), Asia Pacific (Sydney), South America (SÃ£o Paulo), and Asia Pacific (Mumbai).

The environment type LINUX_GPU_CONTAINER is available only in regions US East (N. Virginia), US East (Ohio), US West (Oregon), EU (Ireland), EU (Frankfurt), Asia Pacific (Tokyo), and Asia Pacific (Sydney).
The environment type MAC_ARM is available for Medium fleets only in regions US East (N. Virginia), US East (Ohio), US West (Oregon), Asia Pacific (Sydney), and EU (Frankfurt)
The environment type MAC_ARM is available for Large fleets only in regions US East (N. Virginia), US East (Ohio), US West (Oregon), and Asia Pacific (Sydney).

The environment type WINDOWS_EC2 is available only in regions US East (N. Virginia), US East (Ohio), US West (Oregon), EU (Ireland), EU (Frankfurt), Asia Pacific (Tokyo), Asia Pacific (Singapore), Asia Pacific (Sydney), South America (SÃ£o Paulo), and Asia Pacific (Mumbai).

The environment type WINDOWS_SERVER_2019_CONTAINER is available only in regions US East (N. Virginia), US East (Ohio), US West (Oregon), Asia Pacific (Sydney), Asia Pacific (Tokyo), Asia Pacific (Mumbai) and EU (Ireland).

The environment type WINDOWS_SERVER_2022_CONTAINER is available only in regions US East (N. Virginia), US East (Ohio), US West (Oregon), EU (Ireland), EU (Frankfurt), Asia Pacific (Sydney), Asia Pacific (Singapore), Asia Pacific (Tokyo), South America (SÃ£o Paulo) and Asia Pacific (Mumbai).

nested_items.name: computeType
nested_items.description: Information about the compute resources the compute fleet uses. Available values include:
ATTRIBUTE_BASED_COMPUTE: Specify the amount of vCPUs, memory, disk space, and the type of machine.

nested_items.name: computeConfiguration
nested_items.description: The compute configuration of the compute fleet. This is only required if computeType is set to ATTRIBUTE_BASED_COMPUTE.

nested_items.name: vCpu
nested_items.description: The number of vCPUs of the instance type included in your fleet.

nested_items.name: memory
nested_items.description: The amount of memory of the instance type included in your fleet.

nested_items.name: disk
nested_items.description: The amount of disk space of the instance type included in your fleet.

nested_items.name: machineType
nested_items.description: The machine type of the instance type included in your fleet.

nested_items.name: instanceType
nested_items.description: The EC2 instance type to be launched in your fleet.

nested_items.name: scalingConfiguration
nested_items.description: The scaling configuration of the compute fleet.

nested_items.name: scalingType
nested_items.description: The scaling type for a compute fleet.

nested_items.name: targetTrackingScalingConfigs
nested_items.description: A list of TargetTrackingScalingConfiguration objects.

nested_items.name: metricType
nested_items.description: The metric type to determine auto-scaling.

nested_items.name: targetValue
nested_items.description: The value of metricType when to start scaling.

nested_items.name: maxCapacity
nested_items.description: The maximum number of instances in the ï¬eet when auto-scaling.

nested_items.name: desiredCapacity
nested_items.description: The desired number of instances in the ï¬eet when auto-scaling.

nested_items.name: overflowBehavior
nested_items.description: The compute fleet overflow behavior.
For overflow behavior QUEUE, your overflow builds need to wait on the existing fleet instance to become available.
For overflow behavior ON_DEMAND, your overflow builds run on CodeBuild on-demand.

nested_items.name: vpcConfig
nested_items.description: Information about the VPC configuration that CodeBuild accesses.

nested_items.name: vpcId
nested_items.description: The ID of the Amazon VPC.

nested_items.name: subnets
nested_items.description: A list of one or more subnet IDs in your Amazon VPC.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: securityGroupIds
nested_items.description: A list of one or more security groups IDs in your Amazon VPC.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: proxyConfiguration
nested_items.description: The proxy configuration of the compute fleet.

nested_items.name: defaultBehavior
nested_items.description: The default behavior of outgoing traffic.

nested_items.name: orderedProxyRules
nested_items.description: An array of FleetProxyRule objects that represent the specified destination domains or IPs to allow or deny network access control to.

nested_items.name: type
nested_items.description: The type of proxy rule.

nested_items.name: effect
nested_items.description: The behavior of the proxy rule.

nested_items.name: entities
nested_items.description: The destination of the proxy rule.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: imageId
nested_items.description: The Amazon Machine Image (AMI) of the compute fleet.

nested_items.name: fleetServiceRole
nested_items.description: The service role associated with the compute fleet. For more information, see Allow a user to add a permission policy for a fleet service role in the CodeBuild User Guide.

nested_items.name: tags
nested_items.description: A list of tag key and value pairs associated with this compute fleet.

nested_items.name: key
nested_items.description: The tag's key.

nested_items.name: value
nested_items.description: The tag's value.

nested_items.name: fleetsNotFound
nested_items.description: The names of compute fleets for which information could not be found.
(string) ---
